body:
Hux : You’re irrationally angry on a permanent basis.

Kylo : Well, that’s just your personal opinion because I don’t have anger issues. Anyone else think I have anger issues?

Hux : Well, I wouldn’t really call it an issue. An issue is something you can fix.

25 || Void || They/them || Sideblog. 
Main is dreadmasterstyrak.
Personal blog is chained-screams.
I like drawing fanart of SWTOR, Bloodborne, and World of Warcraft as well as other things, with focus on sort-of obscure characters and lore. So expect a lot of Dread Masters, Valkorion, Scions, Bloodborne bosses, monsters, and my own fan-characters. I don't own any other franchise I might draw art of, their respective owners do. My art is made in appreciation for the characters, locations, items, and concepts present in those games, shows, or books.

summary: The very first designs of the headcanon Dread Masters! Drawn way back in 2013! They are quite different to the ones I have now,...
caption:
The very first designs of the headcanon Dread Masters! Drawn way back in 2013!

They are quite different to the ones I have now, except Tyrans abd Brontes, who didn’t change that much. They all used to have white hair because of the anecdote that extreme stress might cause a person to go gray overnight. I believe exposure of Phobis Devices. They also had ritual scarring that traced the patterns on their masks.

Styrak - Human, gnarly scars, very pale and corrupted, missing eye, short white hair. Used to be married to Brontes. His old backstory was that he was a fallen Jedi hailing from a noble house in northern reaches of Alderaan, and falling when he learned a rival house slaughtered his family. Basically he was space house Stark.

Calphayus - Sith Pureblood, short white hair, mutton chops, orange eyes, some silver jewelry. His design would become more fluffy and a bit more simple in the coming years since I kinda consistently forgot to draw his scars and jewelry to the point of kind of ditching them altogether for all of the dread masters. His old backstory involved him being possessed by Sel Makor and being very blood thirsty and lashing out at people when Sel makor was in control.

Bestia - Sith Pureblood, short white hair in a faux mohawk, yellow eyes, golden jewelry implants on the forehead. Calphayus’s daughter. She kind of got more and more buff over the years. Used to be married to Raptus.

Brontes - Echani or human. Long white hair, very pale. Her initial design had her with her eyes somehow lost and replaced with those gnarly scars but I kind of drifted away from the idea and she had eyes in most of the later drawings. Sister of Tyrans, used to be married to Styrak.

Raptus - Sith Pureblood. Mahogany skin, middle length hair slicked back, orange eyes. He kind of shrunk over time, becoming very small and frail looking. Used to be married to Bestia.

Tyrans - Echani or human. Very pale, white hair, bright red eyes. I kind of just changed his hair at one point to be more fluffy and his face to be longer (learning how to draw human faces better helped too lmao) but otherwise he didn’t change much. Brother of Brontes.

title: Damerey Discord
excerpt: A positive space to share what we love about Poe Dameron and Rey.
description:
It’s still barebones and a work in progress, but the new Damerey discord server is up and running! I hope it will provide a nice, positive space for our wholesome ship. Whether you’re ready to talk you fingers off or just want to lurk, feel free to join!

If you’ve never used Discord before, it is a chat program similar to slack or IRC. You can download the desktop app for PC, use in browser, or use an app on your phone/tablet. Just click the link and it will prompt you to log in or make an account before dumping you into the server!

summary: The blurb for Claudia Gray’s Master & Apprentice is here, giving us just that much more information about the upcoming Qui-Gon...
caption:
The blurb for Claudia Gray’s Master & Apprentice is here, giving us just that much more information about the upcoming Qui-Gon Jinn and Obi-Wan Kenobi novel.

An unexpected offer threatens the bond between Qui-Gon Jinn and Obi-Wan Kenobi as the two Jedi navigate a dangerous new planet and an uncertain future.

A Jedi must be a fearless warrior, a guardian of justice, and a scholar in the ways of the Force. But perhaps a Jedi’s most essential duty is to pass on what they have learned. Master Yoda trained Dooku; Dooku trained Qui-Gon Jinn; and now Qui-Gon has a Padawan of his own. But while Qui-Gon has faced all manner of threats and danger as a Jedi, nothing has ever scared him like the thought of failing his apprentice.

Obi-Wan Kenobi has deep respect for his Master, but struggles to understand him. Why must Qui-Gon so often disregard the laws that bind the Jedi? Why is Qui-Gon drawn to ancient Jedi prophecies instead of more practical concerns? And why wasn’t Obi-Wan told that Qui-Gon is considering an invitation to join the Jedi Council—knowing it would mean the end of their partnership? The simple answer scares him: Obi-Wan has failed his Master.

When Jedi Rael Averross, another former student of Dooku, requests their assistance with a political dispute, Jinn and Kenobi travel to the royal court of Pijal for what may be their final mission together. What should be a simple assignment quickly becomes clouded by deceit, and by visions of violent disaster that take hold in Qui-Gon’s mind. As Qui-Gon’s faith in prophecy grows, Obi-Wan’s faith in him is tested—just as a threat surfaces that will demand that Master and apprentice come together as never before, or be divided forever.

Master & Apprentice will be out in hardcover and eBook on April 16 from Del Rey. (via @quigonsmith)

summary: why tf are men so bitter when things are not for them? there’s all this anger these days about women getting in on things like...
body: why tf are men so bitter when things are not for them? there’s all this anger these days about women getting in on things like the new star trek and star wars and ghostbusters (although of course there have been female star trek fans since day 1) and instead of being happy they’re getting a larger fanbase these manchildren are whining about how suddenly the world does not revolve exclusively around them anymore. cry me a river

blog.name: mandowords
blog.title: Miit'alor
blog.description: I am a descriptivist linguist for the Mando'a language. I show what it can do, not what it MUST do. This is a place for discussion about Mando'a, and Mandalorian society and culture. Feel free to use the head cannons from this blog (or reblogged from others) in your RP or writing. All words and descriptions are taken from the mandoa.org Mandalorian Dictionary. Want to support this blog? Buy me a Kofi? OR buy some Mando'a themed items? Visit our Discord? Blog icon by Rina
